1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:08,180 --> 00:00:10,160
[Jun Ji-hyun]

3
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,070
[Ju Ji-hoon]

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,730
[Sung Dong-il]

5
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:22,040
[Oh Jung-se]

6
00:00:22,380 --> 00:00:24,100
[Cho Han-chul]

7
00:00:25,610 --> 00:00:27,550
[Joo Min-kyung]

8
00:00:27,630 --> 00:00:29,560
[Go Min-si]

9
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:46,950
[Jirisan]

10
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:49,430
[The show is an adapted fiction based on
stories of National Park Rangers.]

11
00:00:49,510 --> 00:00:50,770
[All characters, events, regions,]

12
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:52,120
[organizations depicted in the show
are fictitious.]

13
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,630
The shape has changed.

14
00:00:53,710 --> 00:00:56,740
[-This...
-Someone is going to die there.]

15
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,370
[Dowon Valley, Sumgol Rock...]

16
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:00,770
[There’s been an SOS report from
Sumgol Rock in Dowon Valley.]

17
00:01:00,850 --> 00:01:03,410
[This is a false report. Is this okay?]

18
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,010
[We found the victim!]

19
00:01:05,090 --> 00:01:06,020
[Tilt him more.]

20
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:06,980
[It's him!]

21
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:08,330
The ghost I was talking about.

22
00:01:08,410 --> 00:01:10,090
Could there really be
a ghost on the mountain?

23
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:13,830
If anyone had a strong desire,
they could remain there as a ghost.

24
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:16,100
What if we get caught again?

25
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:18,160
Are we going to starve the kids?

26
00:01:21,310 --> 00:01:22,360
[A potato bomb?]

27
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:24,200
It's kind of like a landmine.

28
00:01:24,289 --> 00:01:25,550
You have murdered my husband!

29
00:01:25,630 --> 00:01:27,900
[It means a civilian died
because of a park ranger's mistake.]

30
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:30,590
I saw a hand.
There were five scratch scars.

31
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:32,600
You think people will believe that?

32
00:01:32,690 --> 00:01:33,820
[I will find that person.]

33
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,960
Do you think it wasn't an accident?

34
00:01:36,050 --> 00:01:36,970
Yes.

35
00:01:38,820 --> 00:01:40,580
[There were five scratch scars.]

36
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:42,930
[I saw a hand for sure.]

37
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:44,150
[I'm positive.]

38
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:52,890
[Town Hall Meeting,
Information Session on Explosives]

39
00:01:52,970 --> 00:01:55,240
[As you know,]

40
00:01:55,320 --> 00:02:00,530
there have been continuous accidents
on Mount Jirisan lately.

41
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:02,340
You can see...

42
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:06,960
This is the potato bomb
that caused the accident.

43
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:10,530
If you ever find something
similar on the mountain,

44
00:02:10,610 --> 00:02:15,150
please don't touch it and
report to the national park immediately.

45
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:17,750
And next...

46
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:22,670
These are poisonous mushrooms
that grow on Jirisan,

47
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,520
such as Common Rustgill and panther cap.

48
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:28,920
Accidents happen when
mistaking them as edible.

49
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:31,780
-So please look at the photos carefully...
-This is ridiculous.

50
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:34,430
You don't have an actual plan,

51
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:37,370
you just want us to be careful.

52
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:42,360
With unrestricted trails,

53
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:44,170
we can remove the dangerous
objects in advance.

54
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:47,070
-But in restricted areas...
-Oh, great.

55
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,620
It's that crap again.

56
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:51,140
Don't go to the mountain.
And don't catch snakes.

57
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:55,260
You've got some tall orders for us,
but you can't even protect us.

58
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:58,780
It's not worth hearing. Let's go!

59
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:00,970
Come on, get up!

60
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,410
Let's get out of here.

61
00:03:06,810 --> 00:03:09,280
We can't just leave like this.

62
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:11,640
There's more!

63
00:03:13,270 --> 00:03:16,470
Please stay and listen.

64
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,550
What? Information Session, my foot.

65
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,230
[Crazy Guy]

66
00:03:45,110 --> 00:03:45,990
Hello?

67
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:49,940
[I found the house missing a potato bomb.
It was Yang-sun's place.]

68
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:51,790
I have something to tell you, too.

69
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:53,890
Let's meet up. Where are you?

70
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:58,590
Okay, I'll come to you.

71
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:05,940
Yi-gang.

72
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:11,150
Hi.

73
00:04:12,450 --> 00:04:15,810
Se-wook, how have you been?

74
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:20,100
Great, yourself?

75
00:04:24,460 --> 00:04:26,060
What happened to your hand?

76
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:33,070
It's nothing.

77
00:04:33,159 --> 00:04:35,840
A raccoon scratched me on the mountain.

78
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:39,790
Well...

79
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:42,650
I'll see you later.

80
00:04:59,990 --> 00:05:02,430
What do you mean,
you saw a guy with scars on his hand?

81
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:04,610
Who was it? Do you know him?

82
00:05:06,710 --> 00:05:08,230
Se-wook.

83
00:05:10,490 --> 00:05:12,170
Lee Se-wook.

84
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:15,200
We grew up in the same village.

85
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:17,550
[But we didn't talk much growing up.]

86
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:22,300
[He was a quiet and shy kid.]

87
00:05:23,050 --> 00:05:26,200
[He was born
and raised here his whole life.]

88
00:05:26,290 --> 00:05:29,310
[He knows the mountain
better than anyone else.]

89
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:32,800
[After his father passed away,]

90
00:05:33,130 --> 00:05:35,400
[he stayed at his cousin
Yang-sun's house for a bit.]

91
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:35,820
[World of Beekeeping]

92
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:40,150
[Now he lives alone, raising bees
near the foot of the mountain.]

93
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,270
That's him, then.

94
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,710
He must have known about
the bomb in the house,

95
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,900
and it would've been easy to take it.

96
00:05:59,970 --> 00:06:02,570
These are all your guesses.

97
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:04,500
There are no security cameras
on the mountain.

98
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:08,910
The police won't believe
that Se-wook left the bomb there.

99
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,550
What about Yang-sun?

100
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,600
She knew that the bomb disappeared, right?

101
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:25,710
They got along well because
they are cousins and the same age.

102
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,400
She might know something.

103
00:06:30,670 --> 00:06:34,700
I've been calling her, but
her phone has been off.

104
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:43,690
[Jirisan National Park
Haedong Ranger Station]

105
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:45,870
What a day.

106
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:51,120
Why do they keep disappearing?

107
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:52,640
First Yang-sun, then Yi-gang...

108
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:55,280
Yang-sun wasn't feeling well.

109
00:06:55,370 --> 00:06:58,980
Is that the latest trend?
The newbie, too...

110
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,700
Kids these days...

111
00:07:02,210 --> 00:07:03,050
Wow...

112
00:07:03,140 --> 00:07:07,000
Perfect timing.
Coming in as we just finished work.

113
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,600
Where's Yang-sun? Didn't she come here?

114
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:12,460
Well, Yang-sun...

115
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:15,900
Hey, I thought you were sick!
You look just fine.

116
00:07:15,990 --> 00:07:18,300
Yang-sun. Where is Yang-sun?

117
00:07:18,380 --> 00:07:22,920
Why are you asking us?
We were out working hard all day.

118
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:26,320
Have you seen Yang-sun?

119
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,750
She left on a patrol car earlier.

120
00:07:34,590 --> 00:07:36,060
What's that?

121
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:39,590
Each patrol car has a forest fire
reporting device installed.

122
00:07:39,670 --> 00:07:42,990
If we track its location,
we'll be able to find where she is.

123
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,440
[Saemagol]

124
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:50,010
It's Saemagol.

125
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:54,840
Yang-sun went to Saemagol? All alone?

126
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:57,440
Hey! Wait for me!

127
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,540
-Where are you going?
-Gosh!

128
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:02,560
Hey! Where are you going?

129
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,180
[Jirisan National Park
Haedong Ranger Station]

130
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:42,720
Are you sure Yang-sun went up to Saemagol?

131
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,690
-The sun will set soon.
-No!

132
00:08:44,770 --> 00:08:46,790
Yang-sun's not like us.

133
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:50,780
You know she fainted
during hiking training.

134
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:53,050
She has a weak heart and
low blood pressure.

135
00:08:53,130 --> 00:08:56,110
Why would she go up a restricted trail?

136
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:59,640
Enough of that.
That's why we're looking for her.

137
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:01,910
Gosh!

138
00:09:26,690 --> 00:09:30,130
But we don't even know
where she went to...

139
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:32,230
So how are we going to do this?

140
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:36,100
Even restricted areas have
frequently walked paths.

141
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:39,160
They're the ones made by animals.

142
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:46,810
I don't know why she came here,

143
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:49,160
but if she did,
she probably took this path.

144
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:54,870
What are you waiting for?

145
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:02,980
Yang-sun!

146
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,960
Yang-sun!

147
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,620
Yang-sun!

148
00:10:16,670 --> 00:10:18,560
Yang-sun!

149
00:10:21,290 --> 00:10:23,050
Yang-sun!

150
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:43,340
-What's that?
-It's Yang-sun's.

151
00:10:44,930 --> 00:10:46,150
Are you sure?

152
00:10:46,490 --> 00:10:49,050
A hiking lady gave it to
Yang-sun to thank her.

153
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:51,610
It was June 19th of last year.

154
00:10:51,690 --> 00:10:53,840
On a rainy day.

155
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,730
It's definitely hers.

156
00:10:58,370 --> 00:11:00,850
At least we can be sure
she went up this way.

157
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:03,330
This leads to the Geombawi Forest...

158
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,010
Jeez.

159
00:11:06,350 --> 00:11:08,120
Yang-sun!

160
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:11,390
Yang-sun!

161
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:17,360
Over there! Yang-sun!

162
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,270
Are you all right?

163
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:28,070
Yang-sun, are you okay?

164
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:45,660
Hold on.

165
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:47,720
Don't move.

166
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:50,070
It's dangerous, Yang-sun.

167
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:54,150
What are you doing?

168
00:11:54,270 --> 00:11:55,780
We have to remove it.

169
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:57,760
Why don't we call someone?

170
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,860
Call who? This is our job.

171
00:11:59,940 --> 00:12:02,590
I'll do it then.

172
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:05,190
Shut it, both of you. Let me focus.

173
00:12:51,850 --> 00:12:52,820
Hurry!

174
00:13:01,980 --> 00:13:03,530
Don't put it in your bag.

175
00:13:04,830 --> 00:13:05,970
Okay.

176
00:13:14,070 --> 00:13:16,170
How did you find this?

177
00:13:26,330 --> 00:13:27,640
Yang-sun.

178
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:33,310
That bomb disappeared
from your house, right?

179
00:13:36,460 --> 00:13:40,110
How did you know?

180
00:13:40,190 --> 00:13:41,870
What are you saying?

181
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:44,270
Did you come here to find that bomb?

182
00:13:44,350 --> 00:13:46,580
How did you know it was here?

183
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,570
Se-wook

184
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:52,710
told me.

185
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:02,330
Se-wook?

186
00:14:03,970 --> 00:14:08,290
He said he saw my grandpa here,
on the day the bomb exploded.

187
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:13,540
Your grandfather?

188
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:19,130
I'm sorry. I couldn't tell you.

189
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:22,070
I wanted to trust my grandpa.

190
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,300
Who's there?

191
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:35,930
Grandpa, I thought you
went to the mountain.

192
00:14:36,010 --> 00:14:39,620
Well, I had to find something.

193
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,920
-Do you need some help?
-No, no.

194
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:48,490
Don't worry about it.
You should get going.

195
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,340
All right, then.

196
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:53,060
Bye.

197
00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:01,500
Until then, I had no idea it was a bomb.

198
00:15:01,590 --> 00:15:04,490
Nor did I know grandpa had such things.

199
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,850
That's when I knew it was a bomb.

200
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:16,500
Homemade bombs used by poachers

201
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:19,520
who hunted moon bears in the 60s and 70s.

202
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:22,170
But I kept doubting it.

203
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:25,910
The bomb could've already been there,

204
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:28,380
and is not grandpa's.

205
00:15:28,470 --> 00:15:29,640
But...

206
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:32,210
You must be tired because of all this.

207
00:15:32,290 --> 00:15:34,980
How did that stupid potato bomb...

208
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:38,300
I’m sorry, but I need
to go to the station right now.

209
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:47,830
What are you doing there?

210
00:15:49,590 --> 00:15:51,360
What did you do with the bombs?

211
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:52,280
What?

212
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:55,310
The bombs that you were holding!

213
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:57,240
Those bombs...

214
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,790
just disappeared.

215
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:00,600
What?

216
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:05,430
I put them back in here, but
I found out today that they're gone.

217
00:16:07,490 --> 00:16:09,000
Are you sure they disappeared?

218
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,350
Why would I lie?

219
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:17,150
-Where did you go that day?
-What?

220
00:16:17,230 --> 00:16:20,080
You've frequented Saemagol
to catch snakes.

221
00:16:20,170 --> 00:16:23,990
You think I killed Mr. Choi
with that bomb?

222
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:27,770
Well...

223
00:16:29,030 --> 00:16:31,170
People might misunderstand.

224
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:34,830
Don't say a word to anyone, okay?

225
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:46,210
I wanted to trust my grandpa.

226
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,850
That's why I couldn't tell anyone.

227
00:16:48,940 --> 00:16:50,790
But I got scared...

228
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:03,680
There were three missing bombs.

229
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:08,510
I came to see if there's any other bomb.

230
00:17:08,589 --> 00:17:10,400
But

231
00:17:13,890 --> 00:17:16,619
I didn't think it would actually be here.

232
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:23,500
Are you sure that trap belongs
to your grandfather?

233
00:17:27,619 --> 00:17:30,180
First, tell the cops everything you know.

234
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:37,200
I know how you feel
but that's the right thing to do.

235
00:17:38,670 --> 00:17:40,560
Okay.

236
00:17:43,620 --> 00:17:46,690
-Can you get up?
-Yes.

237
00:17:49,330 --> 00:17:52,520
Hold on to my rucksack.
It'll be better than walking by yourself.

238
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,510
Be careful.

239
00:18:09,530 --> 00:18:12,940
It's not the grandpa.

240
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:15,160
He doesn't have a scar on his hand.

241
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,640
It's Lee Se-wook.

242
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:20,030
The police will uncover the truth.

243
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:21,920
If it's the grandpa or Lee Se-wook.

244
00:18:28,310 --> 00:18:30,410
I saw the hand for sure.

245
00:18:31,790 --> 00:18:34,690
There were scars on the hand. Trust me.

246
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:38,930
Do you think people will believe that?

247
00:18:50,990 --> 00:18:51,830
Get in.

248
00:18:51,910 --> 00:18:54,100
We'll take you to the police substation.

249
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:56,830
I'll come too.

250
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,190
Return the patrol car and go home.

251
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:53,940
[Haedongsan-ro]

252
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:01,590
Yes?

253
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,580
It was you.

254
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:15,110
What?

255
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,580
The potato bomb.

256
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:19,440
You placed it there in Saemagol.

257
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:22,710
Who are you?

258
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,310
What are you saying?

259
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:30,780
I've never been to Saemagol,
or heard of such a bomb.

260
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:34,260
Leave!

261
00:20:40,190 --> 00:20:42,870
A black T-shirt with white stains...

262
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:46,150
Poisoned yogurt drinks...

263
00:20:46,230 --> 00:20:47,660
Was that also you?

264
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:51,520
Who are you?

265
00:20:51,610 --> 00:20:55,010
Go away. It's not me! Leave me alone!

266
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:04,250
It wasn't me.

267
00:21:05,970 --> 00:21:11,140
So please come to the station with us
and answer a few questions.

268
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:14,670
What questions? It wasn't me.

269
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:16,390
You...

270
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,280
It's...

271
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,340
It's just a formality.

272
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:23,820
We have to do this
since a report has been made.

273
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:37,850
Is that him?

274
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,310
Yes.

275
00:21:49,020 --> 00:21:50,620
That's him, for sure.

276
00:22:04,690 --> 00:22:07,330
[No Entry]

277
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:10,480
[He left the bomb by the grave]

278
00:22:10,570 --> 00:22:13,300
[after we'd left.]

279
00:22:36,060 --> 00:22:37,400
How can I help you?

280
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:41,860
Could I check the security camera
outside the building?

281
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:50,170
[There's no camera on the mountain,]

282
00:22:50,260 --> 00:22:52,990
[but there is one at the entrance to it.]

283
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:56,220
[Channel 2]

284
00:22:56,430 --> 00:23:00,420
[I must prove that he went
to the mountain that day.]

285
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:05,960
[If I can only spot him
in the recordings,]

286
00:23:06,050 --> 00:23:09,660
[I can prove that he's the criminal.]

287
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,100
Thank you.

288
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:25,240
[Not even herb collectors come here.]

289
00:23:25,330 --> 00:23:28,520
And because there are no humans,
it's animal paradise.

290
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:31,080
Animal paradise...

291
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:38,850
Things have been disorderly
due to unfortunate events.

292
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:41,450
But now we must return to our main tasks.

293
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:44,770
Take care of the postponed documents,

294
00:23:44,850 --> 00:23:48,130
check the forest
fire extinguishers before winter,

295
00:23:48,210 --> 00:23:51,280
and patrol with special attention
to the inflammables

296
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:54,470
around each trail and near the park.

297
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,240
Yes, sir.

298
00:23:56,320 --> 00:24:00,100
Yang-sun and Hyun-jo are
on a sick leave today.

299
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:03,750
I thought you'd need help, so
I called Il-hae over from Bidam Shelter.

300
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,560
Help each other.

301
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,030
-Yes, sir.
-Right, keep it up.

302
00:24:15,930 --> 00:24:19,340
I get why Yang-sun's not here.

303
00:24:19,420 --> 00:24:21,560
But the newbie?

304
00:24:21,650 --> 00:24:24,000
You saw him yesterday. He was fine.

305
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:29,500
What's wrong with
Haedong Station these days?

306
00:24:29,580 --> 00:24:31,600
-Accidents and sick leaves...
-Let's get to work.

307
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:34,540
-I just got here.
-Yes, let's work.

308
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:36,770
-Work, Il-hae.
-I want coffee... What?

309
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:38,360
-Il-hae?
-Yes, Il-hae.

310
00:24:38,450 --> 00:24:40,880
How dare you call a team leader by name?

311
00:24:40,970 --> 00:24:42,940
Come here!

312
00:24:44,070 --> 00:24:45,080
Hey!

313
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:58,980
[Fire Danger]

314
00:25:09,820 --> 00:25:11,160
It's behind that...

315
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,850
I can't do all this.

316
00:25:38,380 --> 00:25:40,020
What on earth are you doing?

317
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:44,340
You think you can
just show up at your will?

318
00:25:47,580 --> 00:25:50,730
You can scold me later,
but can we find this first?

319
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:03,750
[Like you said, Saemagol must be
a paradise for animals.]

320
00:26:04,670 --> 00:26:07,400
[There were thirty automated cameras
installed for ecology watch.]

321
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:10,300
[Species Restoration Center - 17]

322
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:14,370
Are you still investigating the case?

323
00:26:14,460 --> 00:26:17,690
Three bombs went missing.
There's still one left.

324
00:26:17,770 --> 00:26:21,300
We must find it before
someone else gets hurt.

325
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:28,020
We only need to search
the day of the explosion. Please.

326
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:32,640
It's so messy here.

327
00:26:33,820 --> 00:26:36,380
You. What's going on?

328
00:26:36,460 --> 00:26:37,930
You said you were sick.

329
00:26:38,020 --> 00:26:40,330
Does he look sick to you?

330
00:26:40,410 --> 00:26:42,380
Kids these days.

331
00:26:42,470 --> 00:26:44,360
Hey, what's this?

332
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,880
Memory cards from automated
cameras in Saemagol?

333
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:48,520
Why did you bring these?

334
00:26:49,990 --> 00:26:52,000
This is really the last time.

335
00:26:52,090 --> 00:26:53,560
Okay.

336
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:54,520
You two help out.

337
00:26:54,610 --> 00:26:57,670
We need to find an illegal hiker
on October 15th.

338
00:26:57,760 --> 00:27:02,250
No way. We already got too much
work on our hands.

339
00:27:02,330 --> 00:27:03,720
I'll take care of the documents.

340
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:07,670
Why are we looking for an illegal hiker?
We can't even check their ID.

341
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:10,360
It's related to Yang-sun.

342
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:13,040
What?

343
00:27:13,670 --> 00:27:15,650
What on earth is going on?

344
00:27:15,730 --> 00:27:17,920
Ten plates of scallion pancake
if you find them.

345
00:27:18,130 --> 00:27:21,860
That's not... maybe plus a wish?

346
00:27:21,950 --> 00:27:23,800
You got it.

347
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:24,930
Okay.

348
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:29,930
So what are we exactly looking for?

349
00:27:32,780 --> 00:27:36,560
-Out of my way!
-You shouldn't do this.

350
00:27:36,650 --> 00:27:42,400
I've gotta ask him face-to-face why
he did that to his long-time neighbor.

351
00:27:42,950 --> 00:27:44,540
We're not even sure it's him.

352
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:47,440
My son...

353
00:27:47,530 --> 00:27:49,670
-It's about our family!
-What are we gonna do?

354
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:53,490
Why did you do that?

355
00:27:53,570 --> 00:27:57,400
How many times do I have to tell you?
I have no information on this.

356
00:27:57,480 --> 00:28:00,710
I must do this. There's been a report.

357
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:03,860
Why didn't you tell us about
the missing bombs?

358
00:28:03,950 --> 00:28:06,050
This is exactly why.

359
00:28:06,130 --> 00:28:08,440
I knew everyone would accuse me.

360
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:11,380
Well, it is fishy.

361
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,400
The bomb was at your place.

362
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:17,550
And it was found in the trap you set.

363
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:19,360
Are you nuts?

364
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:22,850
Why would I put that
dangerous thing in my trap?

365
00:28:22,970 --> 00:28:26,160
Maybe someone left there for me to die!

366
00:28:26,250 --> 00:28:28,890
So you should've reported right away
when they went missing!

367
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:30,360
Look at this mess!

368
00:28:30,450 --> 00:28:33,600
Just write down when they disappeared.

369
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:36,580
I...

370
00:28:51,780 --> 00:28:54,720
Your call cannot be completed...

371
00:28:56,610 --> 00:29:00,600
[Why aren't you picking up? Call me.]

372
00:29:00,690 --> 00:29:03,670
[Someone noticed our plan.]

373
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:05,770
[A man came in a patrol car.]

374
00:29:05,850 --> 00:29:08,500
[It was one of the rangers.]

375
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:21,650
[Happy, Lee Se-wook]

376
00:29:23,070 --> 00:29:25,380
[Kim Hyeon-su, Seo Geum-ja, Lee Jong-gu,
Kim Jin-deok, Lee Geum-rye, Choi Il-man]

377
00:29:27,230 --> 00:29:29,580
Kim Hyeon-su.
Baektogol, Jangseungdae, yogurt.

378
00:29:29,670 --> 00:29:34,200
Seo Geum-ja. Yangseokbong,
Saenyeok Rock, lost footing.

379
00:29:34,290 --> 00:29:38,360
Lee Jong-gu.
Deokseoryeong, Buam Cliff, lost footing.

380
00:29:39,620 --> 00:29:44,030
Kim Jin-deok.
Daeyeong-ri, Narigol, lost footing.

381
00:29:44,110 --> 00:29:46,800
Lee Geum-rye.
Baektogol, Bullet Tree, yogurt.

382
00:29:46,890 --> 00:29:51,460
Choi Il-man. Saemagol, graveyard, bomb.

383
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:05,620
[I'll find out who he is. Don't worry.
Just finish what you need to do.]

384
00:30:10,740 --> 00:30:11,620
[I'll find out who he is. Don't worry.
Just finish what you need to do.]

385
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:17,000
[Kim Hyeon-su, Seo Geum-ja, Lee Jong-gu,
Kim Jin-deok, Lee Geum-rye, Choi Il-man]

386
00:30:26,370 --> 00:30:29,010
Hey, I'll find this person before you.

387
00:30:29,980 --> 00:30:32,960
Well, I won't lose to you.

388
00:30:42,490 --> 00:30:43,500
What?

389
00:30:46,190 --> 00:30:47,410
Did you find something?

390
00:30:55,980 --> 00:30:57,450
This is just feet.

391
00:30:57,530 --> 00:30:59,670
You need at least the chest and up.

392
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:01,650
Location?

393
00:31:01,730 --> 00:31:02,740
[Maebawi Rock]

394
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:04,210
Near Maebawi Rock.

395
00:31:05,170 --> 00:31:08,660
That's not anywhere near the graveyard.

396
00:31:09,460 --> 00:31:12,980
The graveyard?
That's where the explosion happened.

397
00:31:13,070 --> 00:31:15,130
What on earth are you looking for?

398
00:31:15,210 --> 00:31:19,200
What about Geombawi Forest?
Where Yang-sun found the bomb.

399
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:21,510
Is it close to Maebawi Rock?

400
00:31:21,590 --> 00:31:22,390
[Geombawi Forest]

401
00:31:23,530 --> 00:31:27,140
Find it first. Then I'll tell you.

402
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:31,970
But we need to know why
in order to find it.

403
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:56,030
[Kim Hyeon-su, Seo Geum-ja, Lee Jong-gu,
Kim Jin-deok, Lee Geum-rye, Choi Il-man]

404
00:31:59,100 --> 00:31:59,940
Wait.

405
00:32:00,020 --> 00:32:02,170
Why? Did you find something?

406
00:32:04,730 --> 00:32:05,820
Look.

407
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:25,690
What?

408
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:27,110
It wasn't the grandpa.

409
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,160
Well?

410
00:32:29,260 --> 00:32:31,190
Call the police.

411
00:32:36,690 --> 00:32:37,870
Officer Park, follow me!

412
00:32:37,950 --> 00:32:40,340
Oh, my poor son...

413
00:32:41,390 --> 00:32:44,880
[Police]

414
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,810
My poor thing...

415
00:33:20,120 --> 00:33:22,720
You really can't judge a book
by its cover.

416
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:25,790
He seemed so shy...

417
00:33:25,870 --> 00:33:29,860
If it weren't for us,
the grandpa would've been framed.

418
00:33:29,940 --> 00:33:33,050
He must have put the bomb
in the trap on purpose.

419
00:33:33,140 --> 00:33:37,040
It could've been for a different reason.

420
00:33:37,130 --> 00:33:38,050
What?

421
00:33:38,130 --> 00:33:43,010
He might have put it there
trying to kill him.

422
00:33:44,810 --> 00:33:48,000
Nonsense. Why would he do that?

423
00:33:48,630 --> 00:33:50,310
Or maybe...

424
00:33:53,460 --> 00:33:56,030
he was aiming for someone else.

425
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:06,860
Why did Se-wook tell Yang-sun
that her grandpa went to the forest?

426
00:34:10,219 --> 00:34:12,530
[Se-wook told me.]

427
00:34:12,610 --> 00:34:16,860
He said he saw my grandpa here,
on the day the bomb exploded.

428
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:21,690
He led Yang-sun there on purpose.

429
00:34:28,489 --> 00:34:34,920
[Lee Yang-sun, Saemagol, Bomb, Yogurt]

430
00:34:44,790 --> 00:34:46,260
[Happy, Lee Se-wook]

431
00:34:46,340 --> 00:34:48,989
[Seo Yi-Gang]

432
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,190
Thanks for coming.

433
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,880
Of course.

434
00:35:14,020 --> 00:35:17,040
I'm sure you couldn't eat anything
because of what happened.

435
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:35,610
Have some even if you have no appetite.

436
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:43,420
[Probiotic Yogurt]

437
00:35:51,730 --> 00:35:53,710
Nothing will happen to your grandpa.

438
00:35:57,860 --> 00:35:59,330
So...

439
00:36:11,350 --> 00:36:13,150
Drink this and get better.

440
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:50,830
Lee Se-wook!

441
00:36:50,910 --> 00:36:52,250
Go check.

442
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:55,820
It's me.

443
00:36:55,910 --> 00:36:58,220
No, he's not home.

444
00:36:58,810 --> 00:36:59,810
Okay.

445
00:37:11,950 --> 00:37:13,710
By the way, Se-wook.

446
00:37:16,530 --> 00:37:18,460
Are you sure

447
00:37:21,110 --> 00:37:22,160
you...

448
00:37:26,100 --> 00:37:31,520
you saw my grandpa going into
Geombawi Forest that day?

449
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,290
No.

450
00:37:41,350 --> 00:37:42,400
What?

451
00:37:50,930 --> 00:37:53,070
You said

452
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:56,550
you saw him there.

453
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,720
I lied.

454
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,680
To kill you.

455
00:39:05,850 --> 00:39:07,780
Still no answer?

456
00:39:07,870 --> 00:39:10,350
What if something really happened?

457
00:39:10,430 --> 00:39:13,330
Don't be ridiculous.

458
00:39:19,420 --> 00:39:22,650
[Seo Yi-Gang]

459
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:37,700
[Seo Yi-Gang]

460
00:41:15,170 --> 00:41:17,480
[Seo Yi-Gang]

461
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,010
Yang-sun.

462
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:24,200
Yang-sun!

463
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:26,970
Yang-sun!

464
00:41:30,580 --> 00:41:32,550
Her pulse is too weak!

465
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:35,450
A person collapsed. She's unconscious.

466
00:41:35,540 --> 00:41:37,260
It's 109 Haedongsan-ro!

467
00:41:49,270 --> 00:41:50,820
Yes, Haedong Street!

468
00:41:51,960 --> 00:41:52,920
Yang-sun?

469
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:54,770
Yang-sun!

470
00:42:22,620 --> 00:42:24,210
[Protected Area]

471
00:42:33,750 --> 00:42:35,260
We're heading up Narigol now.

472
00:42:35,340 --> 00:42:36,440
Come quick!

473
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:17,550
Yi-gang.

474
00:43:18,940 --> 00:43:20,240
Look.

475
00:43:33,050 --> 00:43:35,280
You go down with the bomb first.

476
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:37,380
I'll look some more.

477
00:43:37,750 --> 00:43:40,820
That's enough.
The police will be here soon.

478
00:43:55,860 --> 00:43:59,380
[Sungjin Hospital]

479
00:43:59,890 --> 00:44:03,160
All right. Call me right away
if anything happens.

480
00:44:03,250 --> 00:44:04,630
What happened?

481
00:44:04,720 --> 00:44:06,860
They haven't found him yet, but they will.

482
00:44:06,940 --> 00:44:08,460
Even if he comes down,

483
00:44:08,540 --> 00:44:11,190
He's on the wanted list.
He can't make it far.

484
00:44:11,270 --> 00:44:12,990
That darn thing.

485
00:44:13,120 --> 00:44:15,510
I took him in after his parents passed,

486
00:44:15,600 --> 00:44:17,860
and this is how he pays back?

487
00:44:17,950 --> 00:44:21,770
This is why you can't be nice to people.

488
00:44:22,900 --> 00:44:25,260
Lee Yang-sun's guardian?

489
00:44:25,340 --> 00:44:26,980
How did it go?

490
00:44:27,060 --> 00:44:29,370
The timing was critical.

491
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:32,230
Fortunately, the operation went well.

492
00:44:32,310 --> 00:44:34,070
But there could be side effects,

493
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:36,680
so let's see for a few days here.

494
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:38,230
Thank you.

495
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:41,550
Please check in at the administration.

496
00:44:41,630 --> 00:44:43,440
Thank you!

497
00:44:44,870 --> 00:44:46,380
I'm her guardian.

498
00:44:47,600 --> 00:44:48,610
I see.

499
00:44:50,540 --> 00:44:53,520
Where's the administration?

500
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:55,330
I'll take you there.

501
00:44:55,410 --> 00:44:56,500
This way.

502
00:44:56,590 --> 00:45:03,260
[Intensive Care Unit]

503
00:45:03,390 --> 00:45:05,950
Thank you. It's all thanks to you.

504
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,560
It wasn't me.

505
00:45:08,890 --> 00:45:10,190
It was him.

506
00:45:15,150 --> 00:45:17,210
You led him well as his senior.

507
00:45:17,290 --> 00:45:19,560
Anyway, I'll call you when we catch him.

508
00:45:20,020 --> 00:45:21,370
By the way...

509
00:45:22,840 --> 00:45:25,520
Did you search his house too?

510
00:45:29,890 --> 00:45:31,530
Of course.

511
00:45:31,610 --> 00:45:37,240
Did you find any yogurt with
mushroom poison in it?

512
00:45:39,300 --> 00:45:40,560
What do you mean?

513
00:45:40,640 --> 00:45:43,710
He killed my colleague up there
a year ago.

514
00:45:43,790 --> 00:45:45,770
Also Geum-rye,

515
00:45:45,850 --> 00:45:48,710
and nearly killed a soldier
on a ruck march.

516
00:45:49,170 --> 00:45:51,520
Look into it when you arrest him.

517
00:45:52,070 --> 00:45:54,290
All will be revealed.

518
00:45:54,800 --> 00:45:58,330
I don't get it. What's he saying?

519
00:45:59,710 --> 00:46:01,640
We need to talk.

520
00:46:01,730 --> 00:46:03,490
[Police]

521
00:46:06,140 --> 00:46:07,520
What's with him?

522
00:46:13,230 --> 00:46:14,200
Here.

523
00:46:15,540 --> 00:46:18,320
-Let's eat first.
-I thought you wanted to talk.

524
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:20,500
I know what you're going to say.

525
00:46:20,580 --> 00:46:22,640
You want me to stop

526
00:46:23,360 --> 00:46:25,120
because no one will believe me.

527
00:46:26,300 --> 00:46:30,120
But I really saw it with my own eyes.

528
00:46:30,200 --> 00:46:34,490
And I can't pretend it didn't happen.

529
00:46:35,450 --> 00:46:38,010
That's not what I wanted to say.

530
00:46:38,690 --> 00:46:41,040
I wanted to apologize.

531
00:46:42,890 --> 00:46:46,410
I was doubtful. I didn't trust you.

532
00:46:47,420 --> 00:46:50,820
But that hand with the scars,
and the poisoned yogurt...

533
00:46:51,710 --> 00:46:53,970
It was all true.

534
00:46:57,040 --> 00:47:00,320
You saved Yang-sun,
and also caught Se-wook.

535
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:05,020
If you hadn't,
more people would have died.

536
00:47:05,690 --> 00:47:07,620
But you stopped that.

537
00:47:09,390 --> 00:47:12,660
If I'd trusted you from the start,

538
00:47:12,870 --> 00:47:17,490
could we have saved
the earlier victims too?

539
00:47:19,340 --> 00:47:22,110
You've been saving people.

540
00:47:22,740 --> 00:47:25,770
Putting in more efforts than anyone else.

541
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,880
I'm sorry.

542
00:47:33,910 --> 00:47:36,560
That'll be ten plates of
scallion pancakes.

543
00:47:36,690 --> 00:47:41,390
And some sweet potato makgeolli
will be much appreciated.

544
00:47:52,140 --> 00:47:54,580
Do you think Se-wook's still up there?

545
00:47:58,690 --> 00:48:01,470
Why did he do such a terrible thing?

546
00:48:02,220 --> 00:48:04,660
Once he's caught.

547
00:48:05,710 --> 00:48:07,600
we'll find out.

548
00:48:33,470 --> 00:48:36,120
[Guryong Falls]

549
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:29,500
[Lee Yang-sun, Saemagol, Bomb, Yogurt]

550
00:49:40,580 --> 00:49:43,520
[Kang Hyun-jo]

551
00:49:43,610 --> 00:49:47,600
[Kang Hyun-jo]

552
00:50:32,370 --> 00:50:34,590
Thank you.

553
00:50:39,930 --> 00:50:41,060
That's better.

554
00:50:44,300 --> 00:50:46,980
You're the lottery girl, right?

555
00:50:48,030 --> 00:50:52,440
I heard you paid a large fine.
You'll end up paying more than you get.

556
00:50:52,650 --> 00:50:56,350
That's why I need to find it.
I can't be just losing money.

557
00:51:01,560 --> 00:51:02,780
But, sir...

558
00:51:04,330 --> 00:51:07,270
Are you really not looking for the ticket?

559
00:51:08,070 --> 00:51:10,290
Don't worry, I'm not.

560
00:51:10,500 --> 00:51:12,520
Then what are you looking for?

561
00:51:15,590 --> 00:51:16,890
Tell me.

562
00:51:16,970 --> 00:51:20,120
I might find it while I look for mine.

563
00:51:23,230 --> 00:51:24,240
No.

564
00:51:25,370 --> 00:51:28,230
This is something I need
to find by myself.

565
00:51:39,900 --> 00:51:42,090
I can feel it's winter now.

566
00:51:43,220 --> 00:51:44,900
It won't be easy to hike.

567
00:51:54,180 --> 00:51:57,790
[Year 2020]

568
00:52:14,090 --> 00:52:15,810
Why? What is it?

569
00:52:17,410 --> 00:52:18,580
Nothing.

570
00:52:22,530 --> 00:52:25,770
Does it really snow that much in winter?

571
00:52:26,610 --> 00:52:28,870
Yes. When it really snows,

572
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:31,520
you can only see the flag.

573
00:52:40,590 --> 00:52:45,090
Mountains are indeed a scary place.

574
00:52:50,670 --> 00:52:53,230
[Jirisan National Park
Haedong Ranger Station]

575
00:53:04,830 --> 00:53:05,880
Gosh.

576
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:09,030
What's all this?

577
00:53:09,110 --> 00:53:13,520
You must be hungry from the patrol.

578
00:53:13,650 --> 00:53:17,050
Wow, thank you.

579
00:53:18,100 --> 00:53:20,830
May I? Thank you!

580
00:53:23,430 --> 00:53:26,750
Wow, it tastes so good!

581
00:53:27,130 --> 00:53:29,900
When did you make all this?

582
00:53:35,690 --> 00:53:38,050
That was amazing.

583
00:53:38,130 --> 00:53:39,600
I'm stuffed.

584
00:53:49,010 --> 00:53:51,990
A few years ago,

585
00:53:52,070 --> 00:53:56,110
Someone died because of a potato bomb.

586
00:53:56,190 --> 00:53:58,210
Have you heard about it?

587
00:53:58,710 --> 00:53:59,680
Yes.

588
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:03,330
I heard about the potato bomb
during the orientation.

589
00:54:03,880 --> 00:54:07,450
Didn't know someone died, though.

590
00:54:11,440 --> 00:54:13,620
Someone left it there

591
00:54:13,700 --> 00:54:15,970
on purpose, to kill people.

592
00:54:16,900 --> 00:54:19,540
Really? Who did that?

593
00:54:20,090 --> 00:54:25,340
Lee Se-wook.
He was a beekeeper near the mountain.

594
00:54:25,630 --> 00:54:28,490
Why did he do that?

595
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:33,490
I don't know.

596
00:54:34,120 --> 00:54:38,610
He was found dead on the mountain
after the crime was unveiled.

597
00:54:44,780 --> 00:54:46,670
But that wasn't the end.

598
00:54:47,560 --> 00:54:51,500
There was someone else. The real criminal.

599
00:54:57,420 --> 00:55:00,280
What do you mean?

600
00:55:01,330 --> 00:55:05,360
More people died
on the mountain after that.

601
00:55:08,760 --> 00:55:11,790
No way. You're joking, right?

602
00:55:11,870 --> 00:55:13,890
Did you just make that up?

603
00:55:24,180 --> 00:55:28,250
Who? Why?

604
00:55:29,340 --> 00:55:30,980
I don't know.

605
00:55:31,570 --> 00:55:34,170
I was trying to find out who.

606
00:55:34,260 --> 00:55:36,480
Then I got into an accident.

607
00:55:39,090 --> 00:55:43,670
Is that why you went to
the snow-covered mountain?

608
00:55:46,770 --> 00:55:49,170
That's why I came back.

609
00:55:49,670 --> 00:55:52,110
To find out who that person is.

610
00:55:55,430 --> 00:55:59,250
Someone is signaling me from
up there on the mountain.

611
00:56:01,890 --> 00:56:04,370
If I meet that person,

612
00:56:04,920 --> 00:56:07,980
I can find out who the criminal is.

613
00:56:09,240 --> 00:56:10,630
Please.

614
00:56:12,350 --> 00:56:14,790
You're the only one I can trust right now.

615
00:56:16,130 --> 00:56:18,230
Can you help me?

616
00:56:24,490 --> 00:56:26,590
What can I do?

617
00:56:27,470 --> 00:56:30,700
Haedong Station's been
in charge of 11 sections.

618
00:56:31,040 --> 00:56:35,160
I've marked the places
we decided to signal from.

619
00:56:37,090 --> 00:56:40,070
You just need to install
the cameras in those places.

620
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:42,880
All right.

621
00:56:45,910 --> 00:56:48,510
I'll be right back. Wait here for me!

622
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:22,060
[If I...]

623
00:59:23,530 --> 00:59:25,880
[If I ever see you again.]

624
00:59:27,900 --> 00:59:30,460
[There's something I must tell you.]

625
01:00:57,020 --> 01:00:58,660
[Jirisan]

626
01:00:59,670 --> 01:01:01,090
[It's a real White Christmas.]

627
01:01:01,180 --> 01:01:02,900
Snow is your worst enemy here.

628
01:01:02,980 --> 01:01:04,660
[It's killer weather.]

629
01:01:05,170 --> 01:01:09,280
[Do you still think that
I made your parents die?]

630
01:01:09,490 --> 01:01:11,720
[Someone's coming
to pick up a lost article.]

631
01:01:11,800 --> 01:01:15,960
[Ever since, Yi-gang's been having
cursed Christmas holidays.]

632
01:01:16,050 --> 01:01:17,940
[A wanted man is assumed
to be on the mountain.]

633
01:01:18,020 --> 01:01:20,290
[Radio me if anything happens.
I'll come right away.]

634
01:01:20,370 --> 01:01:22,180
[Yi-gang, are you all right?]

635
01:01:22,260 --> 01:01:23,480
He's a wanted criminal.

636
01:01:23,560 --> 01:01:25,370
[You said Yi-gang knows him.]

